title: Boys Soccer Roundup for Thursday, Oct. 22
text:
Boys Soccer Roundup for Thursday, Oct. 22 Alyssa Davis, @AlyssaM_Davis 6:14 p.m. EDT October 22, 2015 Boys soccer CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN 1 COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
J.P. Stevens 3, Carteret 1: Austin John, Paul Trevidic, and Alex Corrigan each scored a goal to help No. 16 J.P. Stevens (6-12-1) defeat No. 17 Carteret (8-11) in the preliminary round of the GMC Tournament. John began the scoring in the eighth minute off a pass from Ryan Minor to give the Hawks a 1-0 lead. Trevidic's goal in the 36th minute off a corner kick from Jacob Hausman made the score 2-0 at halftime. Corrigan's goal in the 61st minute off a pass from Sayak Ghosh made the score 3-0. Carteret scored in the 66th minute on a goal from Moussa Diouf. It came off a pass from Wilson Idrovo. 
With the win, J.P. Stevens advances in the tournament and will travel to take on top-seeded South Brunswick on Saturday. 
North Plainfield 5, South Hunterdon 1: Francisco Corral and Allen Gavilanes both netted two goals for North Plainfield (11-2). Ronaldo Garcia had one of this own. Canucks goal keeper Edgar Castenada managed four saves. Jacob von Giebel had the lone point for South Hunterdon (4-10). 
Spotswood 5, John F. Kennedy 1: Dylan Blado scored twice for Spotswood (11-6) while Louis Basile and Robby Nason had a goal apiece. Chargers goalie Zach Rodriguez manged 11 saves. Tim Restauro netted the goal for John F. Kennedy (4-13) while goalkeeper Michael Sandor had 6 saves. 
South River 3, Middlesex 1: Jonathan Franco had two goals and one assist and Nark Miranda tallied one goal and two assists for South River. Anthony Ortiz netted a goal for Middlesex (12-7). Joey Venutolo managed 10 saves. 
Scotch Plains-Fanwood 4, St. Joseph 1: Jordan Cimring scored first for Scotch Plains-Fanwood (15-1-1) 30 minutes into the game on an assist from Alex Ferrara. Six minutes later Raider Zach Halma scored on an assist by Zach Cimring. In the second half Cimring netted a point of his own on an assist by James Tenzer. Rounding out the scoring for the Raiders was Robert Viglione, unassisted. The lone goal for St. Jospeh (9-8-1) was scored by Michael Echeverria. 
Immaculata 3, Delaware Valley 0: Nicholas Fari netted a hat trick for Immaculata (8-7-1). Jonathan Roberts tallied three assists. Anthony Ivanov managed 15 saves. 
Bishop Ahr 2, Edison 1: In the first half Patrick Hartman from Bishop Ahr (14-1) scored off his chest on a corner kick by Fitzgerald Flores. Dylan Cruz scored off a free kick for the Trojans in the second half. Justin Ruetsch scored the only goal for Edison (5-12) on a penalty shot. 
Bernards 4, Warren Hills 1: Nick Neptune netted a hat trick for Bernards (11-2-2). Daniel Schindler rounded out the scoring for the Mountaineers. Mario Ramirez - Oseguera had the lone goal for Warren Hills (8-5). 
Sayreville 5, Highland Park 1: Kevin Sousa led the way for Sayreville (8-7-2) with two goals. Roberto Salgado, Ope Olaloko and Louis Brooks had a goal apiece for the Bombers. Kyle Thieringer had the lone goal for Highland Park (2-13-1) and goalie Farhan Rozaidi had seven saves. 
North Hunterdon 4, Franklin 2: Parker Hughes netted two goals for North Hunterdon (5-7-2) while Brandon Puc and Sean Rooney had a goal apiece. Franklin goalie William Hill had 10 saves (2-15-1).
